shield offers a huge boost for casters-encs specifically who are smart&#xD;
enough to aug theirs with AC, with regards to their own class but no&#xD;
one complains about that because it doesn't make them better than&#xD;
warriors :) ). &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Granted I don't have parse evidence entitled "with DW, with shield" but&#xD;
against things with harsh attack thus really spikey and so so hit%, a&#xD;
warrior is going to mitigate without a shield ok, but it improves ever&#xD;
so much more with a shield that I can feel the difference as the&#xD;
healer- the whole principle with warriors taking the least amount of&#xD;
hits the best of all plate tanks, such that if a mob hits alot shield&#xD;
block reduces overal dps via evasion, but with the shield even when&#xD;
they do get hit, it will be to a lower end DI to minimum hit most of&#xD;
the time. Shield Block + Shield AC benefits all warriors the same way,&#xD;
but it is most effective on AC freaks by far, which is in augs frankly&#xD;
more available to warriors than the best hp augs are :). Its no where&#xD;
near insignificant, Igneous in Tide rarely has to disc alot of things&#xD;
with his shield (hes been wanting to test if he could, and he has done&#xD;
it), because of the extra improvement the shield and block add, and is&#xD;
easier to heal than a hp warrior with a shield, where mitigation &amp;gt;&#xD;
extra hp to be healed. The only problem is that AC can fail a tank (7&#xD;
maximums vs Hatchet the Torturer on average with &amp;gt;60%&#xD;
mins, but one day gets rounded to 4 max hits), HP's dont.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Not saying aggro or dps aren't bad though just that you shouldn't&#xD;
dismiss the tanking gain as insignificant and that you shouldn't&#xD;
compare it to&#xD;
knights (even though they are tanks, they aren't warriors), as thats&#xD;
just the same as comparing overal net gain to casters&#xD;
(just from the mitigation poview) which you can't really compare,&#xD;
comparisons should be with other warriors. Its those % figures of dps&#xD;
taken stated though that spur these comparisons :/ which just can't&#xD;
happen due to variances in gear progression and area of focus- hp or&#xD;
ac, just the same as that quoted figure of 80% of a cleric for druids&#xD;
and stances, it just cant be done due to the differences in gear foci&#xD;
and spells.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
